org.simplity.kernel.comp

Enum ComponentType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ComponentType>
      • org.simplity.kernel.comp.ComponentType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ComponentType>

    public enum ComponentType
extends Enum<ComponentType>
    components are the basic building blocks of application. This is an enumeration of them. Types come with utility methods to load the components
    Author:
    simplity.org

      • loadGroups

        protected static void loadGroups(String folderName,
                                 Class<?> rootClass,
                                 Map<String,Object> objects)
        load all components inside folder. This is used by components that are pre-loaded. These are saved as collections, and not within their own files
        Parameters:
        folderName -
        rootClass - this is typically the abstract class or the main class. Actual components would be sub-class of this. However, they should be part of the same package. we use package of this root class as the package for all components to be loaded. null if the group is to be loaded as name-value pairs.
        objects -

      • startCaching

        public static String getComponentFolder()
